      "text": [
        " أَمِيرُ اَلْمُؤْمِنِينَ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"سُوقُ اَلْمُسْلِمِينَ كَمَسْجِدِهِمْ فَمَنْ سَبَقَ إِلَى مَكَانٍ فَهُوَ أَحَقُّ بِهِ إِلَى اَللَّيْلِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3752 - The Commander of the Faithful (as) said: \"The marketplace of the Muslims is like their mosque. Whoever reaches a spot first has more right to it until the night.\""
        ]
      }
    },
